Executive Profile
John J. Zillmer  Independent Director, Veritiv CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 11 different industries.See Board Relationships62$225,000
Background

		Mr. John J. Zillmer serves as an Adviser of CVC Capital Partners Limited. Mr. Zillmer served as the Executive Chairman of Univar Inc. from May 7, 2012 to December 2012. Mr. Zillmer served in the managed services industry for 30 years. He served as Chief Executive Officer and President of Univar NV since 2009. He served as Chief Executive Officer and President of Univar USA Inc., since November 2009. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Univar Inc., ... since joining it in October 2009 until May 7, 2012. He served as Chief Executive Officer and President of Univar Corporation since October 2009. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Executive Chairman of Allied Waste Industries Inc. from May 31, 2005 to December 2008. He served as an Executive Director of Allied Waste Industries Inc. since May 31, 2005. He served in various Senior Level Positions with Aramark Corporation from 1986 to 2004. He served managerial positions with Saga Food Service Corporation. He served as an Executive Vice President and President of Food and Support Services division of Aramark Corporation from May 2000 to January 2004. He served as President of ARAMARK's Food and Support Services International division from August 1999 to 2004 and ARAMARK's Business Services division from May 1995 to August 1999. During his 18-year career with Aramark, Mr. Zillmer served a number of other senior management positions including serving as President of international activities and business services group. From 1976 to 1986, he served in general management and staff positions with Saga Corporation and Szabo Food Service Company. He served as Regional Vice President of Szabo ood Services until 1986. He held managerial positions with Saga Food Service Corporation. He specializes in Chemical Distribution, Waste Management, Concessions. He served as Chairman of Univar USA Inc. since May 2012. He has been an Independent Director of CSX Corporation since March 6, 2017. He has been an Independent Director of Ecolab Inc. since May 12, 2006. He has been a Director of Pathmark Stores, Inc. since 2005; Performance Food Group Company since 2015 and Reynolds American Inc. since July 12, 2007. He has been an Independent Director at Veritiv Corporation since June 2014. He has also served as a director of Liberty Capital Partners, a private equity and venture capital firm specializing in start-ups, early stage, growth equity, buyouts and acquisitions, since June 2004. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Liberty Capital Partners, Investment Arm. He served as a Director of Casella Waste Systems Inc. from August 10, 2004 to May 2005 and United Stationers Inc. (alternate name Essendant Inc.) from October 21, 2004 to May 14, 2008. He served as a Director of Univar Inc. since October 2009. He serves on the North American advisory board of CVC Capital Partners. Mr. Zillmer was named to National Association of Corporate Directors Directorship 100 in 2016 in recognition of his outstanding contributions to corporate governance. He was recognized by the food service industry in 2002 for his leadership and received Nations Restaurant News' 2003 Golden Chain Award for his consistent focus on achieving the highest standards of customer satisfaction. He holds an M.B.A. degree from the J.L. Kellogg Graduate School at Northwestern University and an undergraduate degree from Marquette University.Read Full Background




